						               													<description>FloriFauna is a card game with three game modes to enjoy with the family, while we get to know a total of 12 species of flora and 12 species of fauna in Argentine Patagonia.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is an ideal gift since its rules are very simple, and invites to generate new game modes in case of being used with small children or older adults.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In game 1 (FloriFauna) we must quickly play our cards among the four piles on the table. Whoever manages to discard all his deck and cards in hand, will have won. Also, if someone finds a pair of Flora or Fauna among the stacks, he must mention them, causing his opponent to move that pair to the bottom of his deck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In game 2 (Revelations) each player also has a personal deck, but no hand is used. Each player, in a clockwise direction, will reveal cards to the table. If any player at any time finds a pair of Flora or Fauna, he can cover them, and thus take them to his area on the table as a trophy. Whoever puts together the most pairs until the cards in each deck run out will have won. If any player incorrectly covers, he will not be able to cover until he passes his turn again.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Finally in game 3 (The Only One), we must go removing cards from the hands of others, to form pairs in our hand and thus discard them. Everyone will try to be without a hand, in order to get rid of it, and only one will be left with a card that does not have a partner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
